definition: Example is a representative form or pattern
Test is a procedure intended to establish the quality, performance, or reliability of something
Desarrollo is the process of developing or being developed
Código is a system of words, letters, figures, or symbols used to represent others
Aplicación is a formal request to an authority for something
Interfaz is a point where two systems, subjects, organizations, etc. meet and interact
Usuario is a person who uses or operates something
Sistema is a set of connected things or parts forming a complex whole
Función is an activity or purpose natural to or intended for a person or thing
Variable is an element, feature, or factor that is liable to vary or change
Objeto is a material thing that can be seen and touched

Clase is a set or category of things having some property or attribute in common, typically used to denote a division of society, such as a social class, or a division of animals or plants, such as a taxonomic class, or a division of programming code, such as a class in object-oriented programming
